        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In Zend_Controller_Action_Helper_ContextSwitch class, postJsonContext() method checks if the view implements Zend_View_Interface and based on that calls getVars() method. The problem is that getVars method is not defined in Zend_View_Interface. So any custom view class, not extending Zend_View_Abstract, fails on this line:\n\n{code:none}\n$vars = Zend_Json::encode($view->getVars());\n{code}\n{code:none}\nif ($view instanceof Zend_View_Interface) {\n            \/**\n             * @see Zend_Json\n             *\/\n            require_once 'Zend\/Json.php';\n            $vars = Zend_Json::encode($view->getVars());\n            $this->getResponse()->setBody($vars);\n}\n{code}"
        },
